  "instructions": [
    "Preheat air fryer to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Cut butternut squash into small cubes and blanch in salted water until tender.",
    "Drain and allow to cool. Sauté garlic with sesame oil for a few minutes.",
    "Add cooled butternut squash, sherry vinegar, and coconut milk to the pan. Stir well.",
    "If using fish sauce, add now and stir again.",
    "Bring mixture to a simmer over low heat and cook until thickened, about 10-15 mins.",
    "Serve hot as a jiam jeen (stir-fried rice noodle dish)."
